 Efficacy measurements Blood samples were collected for complete blood counts (cbc) with differential on days 0, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 17 and 21 of each cycle.

 Day 0 was defined as the day before day one, in cycle 1 it is the base line, and in cycle 2 is day 21 of cycle 1.

 The primary efficacy end point was protective rate of grade 4 neutropenia after chemotherapy (defined as the rate of ANC keeps above 0.

