 Safety assessments Patients recorded their auxiliary temperature daily, and were monitored for adverse events throughout the study.

 Before chemotherapy and in the third week of each chemotherapy cycle, serum hepatic and renal function, electrolysis, urine routine test and electrocardiograph were examined.

 The safety endpoint of this study was incidence and severity of adverse events (WHO grade 1-4), side effects, and changes in clinical laboratory values.

